.Dd 2011-11-03  
.Dt CLUSTER-ADDUSER 1
.Os
.\"----------------------------------------------------------------------
.Sh NAME
.Nm spcm-adduser
.Nd Add a user to a cluster
.\"----------------------------------------------------------------------
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.\"----------------------------------------------------------------------
.Sh PURPOSE
The
.Nm
command adds a user account to all nodes on a cluster.
.\"----------------------------------------------------------------------
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
command prompts for basic information about a new user and performs
all necessary configuration for the user across the cluster, including
creating accounts on all nodes, initializing the user's dot files for
password-less login, etc.
.Pp
.Nm
is run only on the head node, and only after configuration using
spcm-setup is complete.
.Pp
If an LDAP authentication setup is detected on the head node,
.Nm
will attempt to retrieve user information from the LDAP server.
.\"
.\"----------------------------------------------------------------------
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.\"----------------------------------------------------------------------
